<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Automation on Rachid Youven Zeghlache</title><link>https://youvenzful.github.io/tags/automation/</link><description>Recent content in Automation on Rachid Youven Zeghlache</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 15 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://youvenzful.github.io/tags/automation/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>From YouTube to Blog Post: How I Built a Self-Maintaining Website</title><link>https://youvenzful.github.io/blog/2026-02-15-self-maintaining-website/</link><pubDate>Sun, 15 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://youvenzful.github.io/blog/2026-02-15-self-maintaining-website/</guid><description>&lt;p>In this post I walk through the three automation pipelines that keep this website up to date without any manual intervention.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="tldr">TL;DR&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>A daily GitHub Actions cron job fetches my latest YouTube video&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Downloads the transcript using &lt;code>youtube-transcript-api&lt;/code>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Sends it to Claude (&lt;code>claude-sonnet-4-20250514&lt;/code>) to generate a structured blog post&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Commits the Markdown file and triggers a Hugo rebuild&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="key-takeaways">Key Takeaways&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>The whole process takes about 60 seconds from video publish to draft post&lt;/li>
&lt;li>The Claude prompt is the most important part — iteration matters&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Always diff before commit to avoid unnecessary rebuilds&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;h2 id="the-pipeline">The Pipeline&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="step-1-detect-new-video">Step 1: Detect new video&lt;/h3>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#cf222e">import&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#24292e">yaml&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#0550ae">,&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#24292e">requests&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#cf222e">def&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#6639ba">get_latest_video&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">(&lt;/span>api_key&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">,&lt;/span> channel_id&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">):&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> url &lt;span style="color:#0550ae">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#0a3069">&amp;#34;https://www.googleapis.com/youtube/v3/search&amp;#34;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> params &lt;span style="color:#0550ae">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#1f2328">{&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#0a3069">&amp;#34;key&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">:&lt;/span> api_key&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">,&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#0a3069">&amp;#34;channelId&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">:&lt;/span> channel_id&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">,&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#0a3069">&amp;#34;order&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">:&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#0a3069">&amp;#34;date&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">,&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#0a3069">&amp;#34;part&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">:&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#0a3069">&amp;#34;snippet&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">,&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#0a3069">&amp;#34;maxResults&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">:&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#0550ae">1&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">}&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> r &lt;span style="color:#0550ae">=&lt;/span> requests&lt;span style="color:#0550ae">.&lt;/span>get&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">(&lt;/span>url&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">,&lt;/span> params&lt;span style="color:#0550ae">=&lt;/span>params&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">)&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#0550ae">.&lt;/span>json&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">()&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#cf222e">return&lt;/span> r&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">[&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#0a3069">&amp;#34;items&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">][&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#0550ae">0&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">]&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h3 id="step-2-generate-blog-post-with-claude">Step 2: Generate blog post with Claude&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>The Claude API call uses a structured prompt that ensures the output
includes all required frontmatter fields and a consistent article structure.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>